">Manage preferences</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;·&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://marketbrief.example/unsubscribe" style="color:#2563eb;text-decoration:underline;">Unsubscribe</a><br><span style="display:inline-block;margin-top:8px;">Market information only. Not investment advice.</span></td></tr></table></td></tr></table></td></tr></table></body></html>",
  "text": "MARKETBRIEF
Daily Market Brief
Monday, July 13, 2026

Hi Ritoban,

What changed overnight, today’s market mood, and what to watch.

1. MARKET MOOD — FACTS
US market — Neutral: Futures are little changed before the open.
Canada market — Bullish: Energy shares have positive momentum.
Global risk — Medium: Rates and geopolitical headlines remain active risks.

2. WHAT CHANGED OVERNIGHT
1. US futures hold steady
Investors are waiting for fresh earnings and economic data.
2. Oil prices move higher
The move may support Canadian energy producers.
3. Bond yields are little changed
Stable yields limit immediate pressure on equity valuations.

3. KEY THINGS TO WATCH TODAY
Economic data / central banks: Watch the inflation release and central-bank remarks.
Earnings / company news: Review results and guidance from large technology companies.
Geopolitical / macro risk: Monitor energy prices and geopolitical headlines.

4. ETFS TO WATCH
VFV | US large caps | Canadian-listed S&P 500 exposure. | Stable
XIU | Canadian large caps | Tracks banks and energy leaders. | Positive momentum
ZSP | US large caps | A second Canadian-listed S&P 500 reference. | Watch

5. STOCKS TO WATCH
TCS | +0.4% | Technology spending | Sector commentary
SHOP | -0.3% | E-commerce data | Opening volume

MARKETBRIEF VIEW — INTERPRETATION
• Overall tone: balanced ahead of new information.
• Main opportunity: relative strength in Canadian energy.
• Main risk: an unexpected move in rates.

Data timestamp: Jul 13, 2026, 6:55 a.m. EDT
Sources: Official market data (https://example.com/market-data)

Manage preferences: https://marketbrief.example/preferences
Unsubscribe: https://marketbrief.example/unsubscribe

Market information only. Not investment advice.",
}
`;

