  "text": "MARKETBRIEF
Market Close Summary
Monday, July 13, 2026

Hi Ritoban,

Today’s market performance, key movers, and tomorrow’s focus.

1. CLOSING SNAPSHOT — FACTS
S&P 500: 5,655 (+0.4%)
Nasdaq: 18,420 (+0.6%)
Dow: 41,180 (+0.2%)
TSX: 22,745 (+0.3%)
VIX: 14.5 (-2.0%)
Oil: US$81.40 (+0.9%)
Gold: US$2,405 (-0.3%)
USD/CAD: 1.361 (-0.1%)

2. WHAT DROVE THE MARKET
1. Technology shares led indexes higher.
Stable yields supported growth shares.
Affected: Technology, communication services
2. Oil finished higher.
Supply expectations supported crude prices.
Affected: Canadian energy

3. SECTOR PERFORMANCE
Technology | +1.1% | Semiconductor strength
Real estate | -0.7% | Interest-rate sensitivity

4. MAJOR STOCK AND ETF MOVERS
NVDA | +2.5% | Semiconductor strength | Closed near the daily high.
XYZ | -4.1% | Lower guidance | Selling remained elevated.
TCS | +0.4% | Watchlist relevance | Closed in the upper half of its range.

5. EARNINGS AND CORPORATE NEWS
1. A software company raised annual guidance.
Software: The update supported the sector.
2. An industrial company reported softer orders.
Industrials: Demand commentary was the focus.

6. WHAT TO WATCH TOMORROW
Economic events: Watch inflation data and central-bank remarks.
Major earnings: Review results from major banks and technology companies.
Geopolitical / macro risks: Monitor bond yields, oil, and geopolitical headlines.

7. MARKETBRIEF VIEW — INTERPRETATION
• Day’s market character: constructive, led by growth and energy.
• Market breadth: gains were concentrated in a few leading sectors.
• Main next-session risk: unexpected changes in rates or guidance may shift sentiment.

Data timestamp: Jul 13, 2026, 6:55 a.m. EDT
Sources: Official market data (https://example.com/market-data)

Manage preferences: https://marketbrief.example/preferences
Unsubscribe: https://marketbrief.example/unsubscribe

Market information only. Not investment advice.",
}
`;

