  "text": "MARKETBRIEF
Weekly Market Recap
Week ending Monday, July 13, 2026

Hi Ritoban,

What moved markets this week and what matters next week.

1. WEEKLY SCORECARD — FACTS
S&P 500 | +1.2% | +2.1% | Technology strength
Nasdaq | +1.8% | +3.0% | Semiconductors
Dow | +0.5% | +1.0% | Industrials
TSX | +0.9% | +1.6% | Energy and banks
VIX | -5.0% | -7.2% | Lower volatility
Oil | +2.4% | +4.1% | Supply expectations
Gold | -0.6% | +0.8% | Stable real yields
USD/CAD | -0.3% | -0.5% | Firm Canadian dollar

2. THE WEEK IN 5 POINTS
1. Technology led US equities.
2. Canadian energy benefited from higher oil.
3. Bond yields stayed contained.
4. Central-bank guidance remained cautious.
5. Volatility eased despite narrow market leadership.

3. BEST AND WORST PERFORMING SECTORS
Technology | +2.6% | Semiconductor strength
Real estate | -1.1% | Financing-cost concerns

4. IMPORTANT STOCK AND ETF MOVES
NVDA | +5.2% | Semiconductor demand | Expectations remain elevated.
TCS | +1.0% | Watchlist relevance | Monitor technology spending.

5. ECONOMIC AND CENTRAL BANK REVIEW
Inflation | Readings moderated gradually. | Rate expectations changed modestly.
Employment | Labour data remained resilient. | Growth concerns stayed contained.
Federal Reserve | Guidance remained data-dependent. | Markets retained a cautious outlook.
Bank of Canada | Officials noted inflation progress. | Canadian yields were orderly.
Global central banks | Major banks stayed cautious. | Currency moves were limited.

6. NEXT WEEK’S CALENDAR
Tuesday | US inflation report | May influence rate expectations.
Wednesday | Bank of Canada remarks | May clarify the policy outlook.
Thursday | Major bank earnings | May show credit and consumer trends.

7. MARKETBRIEF VIEW — INTERPRETATION
• Current market regime: constructive but rate-sensitive.
• Strongest theme: technology and energy.
• Weakest theme: real estate and utilities.
• Main next-week risk: policy surprises may increase volatility.

8. WATCHLIST SUMMARY
TCS | +1.0% | Technology spending remained the focus. | Stable

